{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place ginger in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down mixing bowl with spatula.","Add pears, lemon juice and sugar then, without measuring cup, cook <nobr>7 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add vanilla and blackberries then, without measuring cup, cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl.","Place milk, cream, sugar, egg yolks, rum and vanilla mixing bowl then mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer batter to a large shallow dish and place brioche slices in to soak for 15 minutes, flipping them over halfway through.","Heat a non-stick frying pan, add butter then fry soaked brioche, 2-3 minutes on each side. Transfer cooked brioche to a plate and cover with a tea towel to keep warm. Fry in batches until all brioche slices are cooked.","Serve hot, 2 slices per person. Top each serving with a generous spoonful of pear and blackberry compote and dust with icing sugar."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","4 pears, peeled, cored, cut in pieces (3 cm)","1 lemon, juice only","20 g brown sugar","2 tsp vanilla extract","200 g blackberries","300 g milk","200 g single cream","75 g caster sugar","3 egg yolks, from medium eggs","8 brioche slices, stale","1 Tbsp rum","50 g unsalted butter","icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r249395","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-lIhUhePL6ds\/XZWeQuho44I\/AAAAAAAAexg\/6ZS-KWE-cnUd1xur3xMy0rg-JofcWwjPQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Whk0gdgdQGVXp7k0.png","title":"Pain Perdu with Pear, Ginger and Berry Compote","publishedAt":"2018-05-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13 g","fat":"39 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"87 g","calories":"3138 kJ \/ 750 kcal"},"usefulItems":"shallow bowl or dish, non-stick frying pan, tea towel, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Before frying the brioche, allow to drain for a few seconds.","Fresh or frozen berries may be used.","You can replace the blackberries in this recipe with in-season berries like strawberries or blueberries.","For a 'crème brûlée' finish, dust the cooked pain perdu with caster sugar and caramelise with a kitchen blowtorch."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","4 portions"]}